The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | DAY III HIGHLIGHTS
                                                                                                                                                                                                     DAY III HIGHLIGHTS
                      
	 Thilan Samaraweera (127) recorded his highest Test score against India. His previous highest was unbeaten 103 on the same ground in 2001-02.         
	 Tillekeratne Dilshan (125 ..) scored his first hundred against India and his fifth overall.         
	 Dilshan scored the fourth hundred of the Sri Lankan innings. It was the third time four Sri Lankan batsmen have scored centuries in a single innings and all three incidents have been at this ground. Mahela Jayawardene has featured on all three occasions.         
	 Sri Lanka notched up a total of 600 in Tests for the seventh time and the third time against India.         
	 It was the eighth instance in Test cricket when four Indian bowlers conceded more than hundred runs in a single innings of a Test.         
	 Anil Kumble went wicketless and conceded more than hundred runs in his spell for the fifth time in Tests. This was, however, the first time against Sri Lanka. The other instances are against South Africa (1996-97), Australia (1999-00), Pakistan (2004-05) and West Indies (2006).         
	 Muttiah Muralidharan took his 150th wicket at the SSC when he claimed the wicket of Gautam Gambhir. He became the first bowler in Test history to claim 150 wickets at a single venue.         
	 Muralidharan has now dismissed Sachin Tendulkar six times in Tests. He joins Glenn McGrath and Jason Gillespie who have also dismissed Tendulkar the same number of times.         
	 Rahul Dravid went past Australian Ricky Ponting to become the sixth highest run-scorer in Test cricket                 COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                      
